1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 d6 { This already tells us where to put our bishop. } 4. Nf3 g6 5. Bc4 { Lining up on the weak spot. } 5... Bg7 6. O-O Nf6 7. d3 O-O 8. Qe1 { Nice to do that first. } 8... a6 9. f5 gxf5 { We don't want to recapture. We wanted to open up our bishop, our rook, and expose their king, and shut down their bishop. } 10. Qh4 fxe4 { The most played, but a mistake! } 11. Ng5 { They only have two good moves. } 11... exd3 12. Rxf6 h6 13. Nxf7 *


